<td valign="top"><font class="body"><b><i>last updated at 06-10-2001 02:01 a.m. (1 times)</i></b><br>Congratulations again Genadine!<p>Determination, Patience, and Perseverance. That is exactly what the Aegis Of Life is .. a badge of dedication and hard work.<p>At one time it was one of the uber cleric and paladin back slot items, and only power players got it (countless of hours of building faction and Grimrot being as much as a 40hour camp per version). But with the advent of Kunark and Velious, the Aegis kinda fell by the way side.. &#39why spend so so much time and trouble on this item when I can get better easier?&#39 Nevertheless, I like to think of it, like the Ghoulbane &amp; Soulfire, as a testamony to ones dedication to their class, something to wear with pride .. I know, how very paladinish <img src="http://www.kor-guild.com/UltraBoard/Public/Images/Default/E13.gif" border="0" valign="absmiddle"><p>On a more personal note, let me thank you, as well, for being part of your quest .. Galathiel and I, both got about half a blue bubble of exp from it (in lvl45) .. hehe, pretty sweet for just handing in a decaying heart! <br>Also, I must confess, I was about as nervous doing this quest with you as I was when I did my Aegis. The horror stories (like Flavius&#39s 1st attempt) of the heart and scythe going poof and getting a &quot;Thank you for your donation to the Temple of Life ...&quot; and no Aegis, were running through my mind.<br>But you did it; I knew you would .. WTG!!!
<!-- SIGNATURE -->
<hr>
Akkanar Sendaria<br>Paladin of Inner Peace and Truth<br>45th Circle Of Virtue
